  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a validator operator, I want to make sure only clients I have approved can use the Engine APIs on Besu\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\nEngine APIs can be configured to require authentication. Authentication is expected to be implemented per [this spec.](https://github.com/ethereum/execution-apis/blob/main/src/engine/authentication.md)\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** When Authentication is enabled, any attempts to connect to Engine APIs are denied unless they have a valid JWT token. JWT tokens issued should expire per the spec, and expired tokens should be denied access. The key to use for signing the tokens should be provided on the filesystem, and its path should be configurable with a new besu option.\r\n\r\n1. Add JWT Auth supporting the algo in the spec. It is not one of the ones currently supported.\r\n2. Require JWT auth on both the HTTP and Websocket stacks that are setup. Assume a hardcoded file path to locate key.\r\n3. Add tests to cover denial of calls with missing tokens, and normal use when it is provided.\r\n4. Add option to specify the path to the key material.\r\n5. If key material is not specified, generate a new one on startup, write it to the file system, and log the location.\r\n6. Update user guide with an engine api specific variation of our[ jwt docs](https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Interact/APIs/Authentication/#jwt-public-key-authentication).",
